<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-577-038  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 577 038.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 18 1990 v4 n24 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IRS' Tax System Modernization: is it enough? (Internal RevenueService)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Levine, Arnold S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Internal Revenue Service's Tax System Modernization programmay not be enough of a revamping of the system to allow the agencyto modernize the most important aspects of tax processing, such asautomating the processing of data on delinquent taxpayersaccounts, auditing procedures, criminal investigations.andP;  Inaddition, the program may not enable the agency to rethink theentire process by which taxpayers pay their taxes.andP;  At issue isthe best way to restructure and, at the same time, remainresponsible to other agencies as well, including the TreasuryDepartment's Financial Management Service.andP;  The current approachto redesigning the program is modular and incremental, graduallyautomating applications at corporate departmental and fieldlevels.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ReorganizationTaxTax PreparationData ProcessingUpdatingUnited States. Internal Revenue Service.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>